  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "There are two general formulations of this problem:",
    "Monocular scenes captured with a single camera moving around a moving object (Pumarola et al. 2021; Yan et al. 2023; Park et al. 2023) 2.",
    "MVS scenes containing a single action captured using multiple cameras which are often static (Sabater et al. 2017; Broxton et al. 2020; Li et al. 2022) There is a third formulation that has been considered (Fridovich-Keil et al. 2023), forward facing scenes where a single camera is bounded to a single plane of motion.",
    "However this has been weakly adopted as a universal paradigm.",
    "For example, K-Planes (Fridovich-Keil et al. 2023) mimics the general consensus on using normalized device coordinates (NDC) and scene-contraction used in Barron et al. (2022) to \"hack\" at this problem."
  ],
